1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:03,509
AI often starts too quickly from an incomplete prompt.

2
00:00:03,509 --> 00:00:07,836
Lumixia Brief adds a deliberate alignment step before work begins.

3
00:00:07,836 --> 00:00:13,798
I built this product during OpenAI Build Week with Codex using GPT-5.6.

4
00:00:13,798 --> 00:00:16,538
A founder starts with one vague sentence.

5
00:00:16,538 --> 00:00:22,067
The private workspace is protected by Google sign-in
and mandatory authenticator verification.

6
00:00:22,067 --> 00:00:25,240
Lumixia asks one focused question at a time.

7
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:27,596
Nothing runs while the user types.

8
00:00:27,596 --> 00:00:31,900
On submit, GPT-5.6 Sol runs through Codex on my computer.

9
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:35,900
It extracts facts, assumptions, contradictions, and evidence,

10
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:39,218
then chooses the most important next question.

11
00:00:39,218 --> 00:00:43,500
The server, not the model, scores eight dimensions:

12
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:48,930
problem, audience, outcome, scope, constraints,
timeline, risks, and success criteria.

13
00:00:48,930 --> 00:00:53,100
Here, one answer makes the problem and audience clear,

14
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:57,331
surfaces an assumption, and raises confidence from zero to thirty-eight percent.

15
00:00:57,331 --> 00:01:04,086
After five adaptive turns, alignment improved
from thirty-three to ninety-two percent.

16
00:01:04,086 --> 00:01:09,200
The structured brief separates goals, deliverables, non-goals,
constraints, risks, assumptions, and open questions.

17
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:14,254
It also captures decisions requiring approval and next steps.

18
00:01:14,254 --> 00:01:17,271
Every claim stays tied to interview evidence.

19
00:01:17,271 --> 00:01:22,992
The user can revise any section, but only an immutable
approved snapshot can leave Lumixia.

20
00:01:22,992 --> 00:01:27,500
Editing an approved brief creates a new revision
instead of rewriting history.

21
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:30,108
Notion receives only the approved version.

22
00:01:30,108 --> 00:01:37,007
Synchronization is idempotent, so retrying updates the same page
instead of creating duplicates.

23
00:01:37,007 --> 00:01:44,555
Codex scaffolded, implemented, tested, and hardened
the React, Express, Supabase, and Notion stack.

24
00:01:44,555 --> 00:01:49,300
The repository records every milestone, pull request, CI result,

25
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:54,134
and the primary feedback session ID without exposing prompts or personal data.

26
00:01:54,134 --> 00:02:00,769
This live demo uses GPT-5.6 Sol through my Codex plan,
not a paid API key.

27
00:02:00,769 --> 00:02:06,887
Lumixia Brief turns ambiguity into a visible,
human-approved handoff before AI work begins.
